org.ndnx.ndn.profiles.security.access.group
Class GroupAccessControlProfile

java.lang.Object
  org.ndnx.ndn.profiles.security.access.AccessControlProfile
      org.ndnx.ndn.profiles.security.access.group.GroupAccessControlProfile
All Implemented Interfaces:
NDNProfile
public class GroupAccessControlProfile
extends AccessControlProfile
implements NDNProfile

This is a sub-Profile of AccessControlProfile defining naming conventions used in a group-based access control scheme (where one can create Groups of users and other groups, and give rights to nametrees based on group membership). For descriptions of data, and how this access control system functions, see the separate NDNx Access Control Specifications Document. This class specifies how a number of access control elements are named: - users, and their keys - groups, and their keys - access control lists (ACLs) - node keys, and their encryption under ACL member keys - if used, markers indicating where to find ACLs/node keys
